Script,OpenAndRebid
window.currentPBSScenario = 'OpenAndRebid';
window.currentPBSScenarioFilename = 'Open_and_Rebid';
console.log('PBS: Logging scenario selection for OpenAndRebid');
fetch('https://bba.harmonicsystems.com/api/scenario/select', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: {
        'Content-Type': 'application/json',
        'X-Client-Version': '1.0.0'
    },
    body: JSON.stringify({
        scenario: 'OpenAndRebid',
        user: whoAmI() || 'anonymous'
    })
}).then(function(r){ console.log('PBS: Server response', r.status); }).catch(function(e){ console.log('PBS: Fetch error', e); });
setDealerCode(`

/*
convention-card-ns: Basic-Bridge
convention-card-ew: Basic-Bridge
auction-filter: Auction.....\n1[CD] +Pass +1[DHS] +Pass +(1[HSN]|2N|[23][CDHS])
*/
# curate: kind=bidding
# convention-card-ns: Basic-Bridge
# convention-card-ew: Basic-Bridge


dealer south

### Imported Leveling Code ###
c1 = hascard(west,2C)
c2 = hascard(east,2D)
c3 = hascard(west,3C)
c4 = hascard(east,3D)

keep06 = c1 and c2          // this is used later w/c3 & c4 expressions
keep44 = c3 or c4           // this is used later w/c1 & c2 expressions

keep015 = keep06 and c3
keep03 = keep06 and keep44
keep045 = keep06 and not c3
####06 = c1 and c2
keep11 = c1 and keep44
keep14 = c1 and not keep44
keep19 = c1 and not c2
keep25 = c1
keep30 = keep06 or c3
keep33 = c1 or (c2 and keep44)
####44 = c3 or c4
keep47 = keep44 or keep06

keep53 = not keep47
keep56 = not keep44
keep67 = not keep33
keep70 = not keep30
keep75 = not keep25
keep81 = not keep19
keep86 = not keep14
keep89 = not keep11
keep94 = not keep06
keep955 = not keep045
keep97 = not keep03
keep985 = not keep015
keep   = 1
keep0  = 0
### End of Imported Leveling Code ###

# ---- South's hand TYPE is the whole lesson: what is my prepared rebid? ----
sHcp = hcp(south)

# Balanced = 4333, 4432, or 5332 (no singleton/void, at most one doubleton)
balanced = shape(south, any 4333 + any 4432 + any 5332)

# No 5-card major -> opener starts with a minor and rebids notrump
noFiveMajor = spades(south) < 5 and hearts(south) < 5

# Bucket 1  Balanced 12-14  ->  open 1m, rebid 1NT
balMin = balanced and noFiveMajor and sHcp > 11 and sHcp < 15

# Bucket 2  Balanced 18-19  ->  open 1m, jump-rebid 2NT
balBig = balanced and noFiveMajor and sHcp > 17 and sHcp < 20

# Bucket 3  Unbalanced -> open longest minor, rebid the second suit naturally.
#   A singleton or void, and a 5+ card minor to open and rebid around.
minorLong = clubs(south) > 4 or diamonds(south) > 4
hasShort  = spades(south) < 2 or hearts(south) < 2 or diamonds(south) < 2 or clubs(south) < 2
unbal = noFiveMajor and minorLong and hasShort and sHcp > 11 and sHcp < 19

southHand = balMin or balBig or unbal

# ---- Responder: 6-11 HCP so partner responds and South gets to rebid ----
northHand = hcp(north) > 5 and hcp(north) < 12

# ---- Quiet opponents keep the focus on opener's rebid ----
eHcp = hcp(east) < 11
wHcp = hcp(west) < 11

# ---- Level the three hand-type buckets so each shows up (18-19 is rare, keep it all) ----
levBalMin = balMin and keep47
levBalBig = balBig and keep
levUnbal  = unbal  and keep47
levelTheDeal = levBalMin or levBalBig or levUnbal

southHand and northHand and eHcp and wHcp and levelTheDeal

action printoneline,
average "South HCP avg      " hcp(south),
average "Bal 12-14 (reb 1N) " 100 * balMin,
average "Bal 18-19 (reb 2N) " 100 * balBig,
average "Unbalanced (2nd)   " 100 * unbal,
`, "S", true)
Script
Button,Basic Open & Rebid,\n\
--- Basic: Open，then Plan Your Rebid (beginner)\n\
South opens one of a minor. The lesson: before you open，notice your hand TYPE，because\n\
that decides your rebid. Plan the rebid first，then open.\n\
\n\
Two hand types:\n\
• Balanced (4333，4432，or 5332 -- no singleton or void，at most one doubleton)\n\
  Rebid notrump to show the balanced shape and the point range:\n\
  • 12-14 HCP: open a minor，rebid 1NT      (e.g. 1!C-1!S-1NT)\n\
  • 18-19 HCP: open a minor，jump to 2NT     (e.g. 1!C-1!H-2NT)\n\
  (15-17 balanced would open 1NT and is not in this set.)\n\
• Unbalanced (a singleton or void，with a long suit or two)\n\
  Bid your suits naturally: open your longest suit，then rebid your second-longest.\n\
  Open the HIGHER of two long suits so the rebid is cheap and does not reverse\n\
  (e.g. with both minors，open 1!D so you can rebid 2!C).\n\
\n\
Reference: https://www.advinbridge.com/this-week-in-bridge/637\n\
4NT is Blackwood，asking for aces，or quantitative (inviting 6NT) after a natural notrump bid. Responses:\n\
  • 5!C = 0 or 4 aces\n\
  • 5!D = 1 ace\n\
  • 5!H = 2 aces\n\
  • 5!S = 3 aces\n\
  • 5NT then asks for kings the same way\n\
%OpenAndRebid%
